{"abstract":[{"text":"Use implicit pointer casting or bridging when calling functions that takes pointers","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"as parameters.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When calling a function that takes a pointer as a parameter, you can use implicit"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"casting to pass a compatible pointer type or implicit bridging to pass a pointer"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to a variable or the contents of an array."}]},{"level":3,"anchor":"Pass-a-Constant-Pointer-as-a-Parameter","text":"Pass a Constant Pointer as a Parameter","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When you call a function that is declared as taking an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UnsafePointer<Type>"},{"type":"text","text":" argument,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"you can pass any of the following:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UnsafePointer<Type>"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UnsafeMutablePointer<Type>"},{"type":"text","text":", or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AutoreleasingUnsafeMutablePointer<Type>"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"value, which is implicitly cast to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UnsafePointer<Type>"},{"type":"text","text":" as necessary."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"String"},{"type":"text","text":" value, if "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Type"},{"type":"text","text":" is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Int8"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UInt8"},{"type":"text","text":". The string is automatically converted"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to UTF8 in a zero-terminated buffer, and a pointer to that buffer is passed to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"function."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An in-out expression that contains a mutable variable, property, or subscript reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of type "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Type"},{"type":"text","text":", which is passed as a pointer to the address of the left-hand side"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"identifier."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"[Type]"},{"text":" value, which is passed as a pointer to the start of the array.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The pointer you pass to the function is only guaranteed to be valid for the duration"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of the function call. Do not persist the pointer and access it after the function"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"has returned."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This example shows the different ways that you can call the a function that takes","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a constant pointer:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["func takesAPointer(_ p: UnsafePointer<Float>) {","    \/\/ ...","}","","var x: Float = 0.0","takesAPointer(&x)","takesAPointer([1.0, 2.0, 3.0])"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When you call a function that takes an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UnsafeRawPointer"},{"type":"text","text":" argument, you can pass"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the same operands as "},{"code":"UnsafePointer<Type>","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", but with any type as ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Type"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This example shows the different ways that you can call a function that takes a constant"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"raw pointer:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["func takesARawPointer(_ p: UnsafeRawPointer?)  {","    \/\/ ...","}","","var x: Float = 0.0, y: Int = 0","takesARawPointer(&x)","takesARawPointer(&y)","takesARawPointer([1.0, 2.0, 3.0] as [Float])","let intArray = [1, 2, 3]","takesARawPointer(intArray)","takesARawPointer(\"How are you today?\")"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"heading","text":"Pass a Mutable Pointer as a Parameter","level":3,"anchor":"Pass-a-Mutable-Pointer-as-a-Parameter"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When you call a function that is declared as taking an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UnsafeMutablePointer<Type>"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"argument, you can pass any of the following:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UnsafeMutablePointer<Type>"},{"type":"text","text":" value."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An in-out expression of type "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Type"},{"type":"text","text":" that contains a mutable variable, property,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"or subscript reference, which is passed as a pointer to the address of the mutable","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"value.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"An in-out expression of type ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"[Type]"},{"type":"text","text":" that contains a mutable variable, property,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"or subscript reference, which is passed as a pointer to the start of the array, and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is lifetime-extended for the duration of the call."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This example shows the different ways that you can call a function that takes a mutable","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"pointer:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["func takesAMutablePointer(_ p: UnsafeMutablePointer<Float>) {","    \/\/ ...","}","","var x: Float = 0.0","var a: [Float] = [1.0, 2.0, 3.0]","takesAMutablePointer(&x)","takesAMutablePointer(&a)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When you call a function that is declared as taking an "},{"code":"UnsafeMutableRawPointer","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"argument, you can pass the same operands as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UnsafeMutablePointer<Type>"},{"type":"text","text":", but for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"any type as "},{"code":"Type","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This example shows the different ways that you can call a function that takes a mutable"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"raw pointer:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["func takesAMutableRawPointer(_ p: UnsafeMutableRawPointer?)  {","    \/\/ ...","}","","var x: Float = 0.0, y: Int = 0","var a: [Float] = [1.0, 2.0, 3.0], b: [Int] = [1, 2, 3]","takesAMutableRawPointer(&x)","takesAMutableRawPointer(&y)","takesAMutableRawPointer(&a)","takesAMutableRawPointer(&b)"]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Pass-an-Autoreleasing-Pointer-as-a-Parameter","text":"Pass an Autoreleasing Pointer as a Parameter","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When you call a function that is declared as taking an ","type":"text"},{"code":"AutoreleasingUnsafeMutablePointer<Type>","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"you can pass any of the following:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"An ","type":"text"},{"code":"AutoreleasingUnsafeMutablePointer<Type>","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" value.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An in-out expression that contains a mutable variable, property, or subscript reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of type "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Type"},{"type":"text","text":". The value of the operand is copied bitwise into a temporary nonowning"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"buffer. The address of that buffer is passed to the callee, and on return, the value"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in the buffer is loaded, retained, and reassigned into the operand."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Unlike with other pointer types, you can’t use an array as an implicitly bridged"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parameter."}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Pass-a-Function-Pointer-as-a-Parameter","text":"Pass a Function Pointer as a Parameter","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When calling a function that takes a C function pointer argument, you can pass a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"top-level Swift function, a closure literal, a closure declared with the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@convention(c)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"attribute, or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":". You can also pass a closure property of a generic type or a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"generic method as long as no generic type parameters are referenced in the closure’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"argument list or body."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For example, consider Core Foundation’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CFArrayCreateMutable(_:_:_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" function."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CFArrayCreateMutable(_:_:_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" function takes a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CFArrayCallBacks"},{"type":"text","text":" structure,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"which is initialized with function pointer callbacks:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["func customCopyDescription(_ p: UnsafeRawPointer?) -> Unmanaged<CFString>? {","    \/\/ return an Unmanaged<CFString>? value","}","","var callbacks = CFArrayCallBacks(","    version: 0,","    retain: nil,","    release: nil,","    copyDescription: customCopyDescription,","    equal: { (p1, p2) -> DarwinBoolean in","        \/\/ return Bool value","    }",")","var mutableArray = CFArrayCreateMutable(nil, 0, &callbacks)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In this example, the "},{"code":"CFArrayCallBacks","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" initializer uses ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" values as arguments","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"for the ","type":"text"},{"code":"retain","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"release","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" parameters, the ","type":"text"},{"code":"customCopyDescription(_:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" function","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"as the argument for the ","type":"text"},{"code":"customCopyDescription","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" parameter, and a closure literal","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"as the argument for the ","type":"text"},{"code":"equal","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" parameter.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Only Swift function types with C function reference calling convention may"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"be used for function pointer arguments. Like a C function pointer, a Swift function"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"type with the "},{"code":"@convention(c)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" attribute does not capture the context of its surrounding"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"scope."}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swift\/calling-functions-with-pointer-parameters"]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/calling-functions-with-pointer-parameters","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"title":"Calling Functions With Pointer Parameters","role":"article","roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"Swift"}]},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift","doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/swift-standard-library","doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/manual-memory-management"]]},"kind":"article","references":{"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/manual-memory-management":{"title":"Manual Memory Management","abstract":[{"text":"Allocate and manage memory manually.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/manual-memory-management","url":"\/documentation\/swift\/manual-memory-management","role":"collectionGroup","type":"topic"},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/swift-standard-library":{"url":"\/documentation\/swift\/swift-standard-library","role":"collectionGroup","title":"Swift Standard Library","type":"topic","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/swift-standard-library","abstract":[{"text":"Solve complex problems and write high-performance, readable code.","type":"text"}]},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift":{"type":"topic","title":"Swift","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Build apps using a powerful open language."}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/swift","role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift"}}}